  "intro": "Three rings, one sight-line. Read the marks from the high platforms, set the orbs, then hold the meridian together.",
  "designNotes": "Orrery alignment. em1 fires north (-z) along x=0,y=3.6 toward rec1; three ring-occluders sit on that line at z=6/0/-6, each vanishing only at its own rotator's correct state — ringX at state 3, ringY at state 1, ringZ at state 2. Each correct state is legible as a pip-count on a DIFFERENT elevated gallery: the ringZ gallery (2 pips) is reachable directly off the north ledge, but the ringX gallery (east, 3 pips) and ringY gallery (west, 1 pip) can only be crossed to while a partner stands on liftA / liftB to raise the lift bridges — asymmetric-info: the reader calls states down to the operator at the rotator row while the wave harasses. Align all three rings so the beam threads to rec1, then both players hold syncA and syncB together by the gate with all enemies down. Families in solved: mechanism (rotators) + beam-item (receiver) + mass (plates) + combat.",
  "fog": { "color": "#252043", "density": 0.026 },
